</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unicophorus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nicophorus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://homepages.go.com/~aela_eq/Shield.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Less Talk, More Fight</span><br>  Posts: 816<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/24/01 12:45:24 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://homepages.go.com/~aela_eq/Shield.gif border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My Final Musings on Rotations, hopefully…</span><hr size=1> The problems with the Planes exist, they just aren't really talked about quite as frequently.  Note... the Plane system does work.  Adun does a great job with it.  I can and have used the system both as a guest and recently as a leader for raids.  However:<br>
<br>
- Talk to the European Guilds or Asian Guilds for whom every raid reservation carries the reality of a partially popped (or worse a potentially fully depopped zone) based simply on a timescale problem.  Yes, we try to keep it from happening and yes, they represent a 'smaller' portion of the playerbase (and do benefit from the timezone difference in other ways).  But... it's a problem, small/large/indifferent is a matter of perspective.<br>
<br>
- Hate second floor.  Not even close to well utilized during the week and requiring most weekend raids to live (as in do a 10 hour minimum raid) in the plane to get there for a day.  Again, not specifically a problem, more a side effect of our system.<br>
<br>
- Fear Gods.  Silent Redemption can do CT.  Watchers can do CT.  Enshadowed probably can... not sure about who else can.  Those three guilds have close to zero use for the planes themselves.  There's a pretty good split opinion right now between folks who think it's perfectly fine for SR, Watchers, etc. to tail after a scheduled raid (which I'm good with) and folks thinking its downright wrong for them to do so and that they should reserve the plane just like everyone else (which to me seems like a hellacious waste of a plane for one god).<br>
<br>
- Two week rule.  There's a lot of talk about three weeks, maybe only one reservation for the two main planes in a two week period, etc.  Its that way because the Planes are as crowded as the Dragons... we just manage to keep a blinder on the 'backlog' because we cut off the list at 14 (two weeks).  A similar approach to Dragons might work (cut Dragon list off at four guilds/raids), but then again... that's an arbitrary change... so is FCFS/FFA...<br>
<br>
Had the planes not been tweaked recently, odds are things would have sorted themselves out exactly like you're saying Twiggie... people would have moved on to Velious or Kunark since planar armor is pretty passe post level 53(ish)... but now the planes are tweaked and the 55+ crowd wants, needs, and frankly are the only ones who can use parts of a zone really built for the 46-53 range (well 46-50 once upon a day...).<br>
<br>
Realistically, the Planes have an aweful lot in common with Fire Giants now.  They (1) represent a resource that has 'needs' for the &gt;55 crowd AND the below 55 crowd (2) the stuff for the 55+ crowd cant' really be accessed until the 55- content is somewhat dealt with, (3) I'm pretty sure a well tuned team or two teams of 55-60 could handle the bulk of most of Hate or Fear, (4) the nature of the items the 55- MoBs drop make it impractical for the 55+ groups to waste time on (most are so far past their planar armor it isn't funny), and (5) Epic pieces are involved (granted, clerics get a special nod because...well they're clerics and... that cleric epic is the most community and team friendly item ever made).  <br>
<br>
As a server we've not looked at the Planes as similar, but they are.  While I'm pretty sure the notion of a FCFS/FFA Plane is too extreme right now for Brell Serilis, the notion of it isn't THAT extreme in general terms... we're just not there... yet.<br>
