</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaveonsilverstring.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daveon Silverstring</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/25/01 12:24:26 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.com/mcheeks/everquest/daveon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My Final Musings on Rotations, hopefully?</span><hr size=1> I'm on the side of having the guilds that can kill CT come in after a normal Fear raid is over to kill CT.  I don't really see a problem with Fear if everyone (or at least almost everyone) finds this acceptable.<br>
<br>
Hate, on the other hand, has plenty of upper 50 content.  Perhaps we can rediscuss splitting Hate into two different reservations per day (first floor/second floor reservations). I think there are already some guilds skipping parts of the first floor just so they can do the second.<br>
<br>
Perhaps an experiment should be run in game to see if we can have two different raiding parties each working on a different floor.  Find a guild during the week that is only going to do the first floor, have them clear enough of the first floor so raiders can get up to the second floor, and have the second raid go up there (first floor would continue their raid, of course).  It would help provide evidence as to how many people can be there at once, and if there are any special precautions that need to be taken when there are two raiding parties there.<br>
<br>
I suspect that two raiding parties of 30-36 people each could work in Hate without massive linkdeaths (as long as people are using /serverfilter and all the other anti-LD settings available).<br>
<br>
Also, even though I don't like the idea of FCFS for the planes, I think we should also attempt to put multiple 12-18 person mini-raids up in Hate in different areas of the first floor to see if it is viable to have people &quot;camp the planes&quot;, as might happen if the planes went FCFS.<br>
<br>
<br>
